Key Match Events: Marko Arnautovic scored a goal off the underside of the bar to give Austria the lead
Julian Ryerson's delivery led to a controversial set-piece goal for Norway to equalize
Christoph Baumgartner was felled by Andreas Hanche-Olsen, resulting in a penalty for Austria
Marko Arnautovic confidently converted the penalty to give Austria the lead again
Philipp Lienhart scored a towering header from Romano Schmid’s corner to double Austria's lead
Stefan Posch headed home from Marcel Sabitzer’s cross to make it 3-1 for Austria
Michael Gregoritsch scored minutes after coming off the bench to make it 4-1 for Austria
A fifth goal was added by Sabitzer, with Gregoritsch providing the assist
Miscellaneous Highlights: In the continued absence of Martin Odegaard, Norway talisman Erling Haaland was wearing the captain’s armband
The match was played in Linz, Austria
